  "response": "The argument for Donald Trump being a clone of General Patton would be surprising and, frankly, unfounded. There is no credible evidence to support such a claim. General George S. Patton was a World War II military leader who died in 1945, long before cloning technology was even a remote possibility. Donald Trump, born in 1946, is a former President of the United States and a public figure with a well-documented life history.\n\nAny suggestion that Trump is a clone of Patton would fall into the realm of conspiracy theories or science fiction, rather than fact-based discourse. It's important to approach such claims with skepticism and to seek out verified information from reputable sources.",
